From 28b670580171fb1ac5847c682b33f4329a8f81f6 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: ESTI Contributors <esti@example.local>
Date: Sat, 13 Jun 2026 07:35:03 +0530
Subject: [PATCH 5/5] Dashboard: zone-header tiles with arrows, coloured square
 tags
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

- Zone headers (Financial health, Project health, Client signals, Team
  performance, etc.) are now full-width ZoneTile components instead of plain
  text. Where a zone maps to one page, it is a ClickableTile with an
  ArrowRight that navigates there; otherwise a plain Tile (Action Center keeps
  its status tag, Quality intelligence / Statutory headers stay non-clickable)
- Clickable tiles show an ArrowRight icon instead of a bottom "Open X" ghost
  button: KPI chips (corner arrow), Ready-to-bill tile, filing tiles, activity
  feed, and team cards. Removed all "Open invoices/projects/clients/filing/
  Activity Center" text buttons — the arrow is the affordance
- Tags restored to semantic fill colours (green/red/magenta/blue/teal + band/
  risk/capacity maps) instead of monochrome outline; square corners stay via
  the global border-radius:0 override. Per-card health edge unchanged
- Dropped the now-unused .esti-zone-head spacing helper (zone tiles sit flush
  in the condensed mosaic)

Co-Authored-By: Codex Opus 4.8 <noreply@anthropic.com>
